WEBVTT

00:01.435 --> 00:02.401
<i> Adult mark: For most folks,</i>

00:02.470 --> 00:04.903
<i> Christmas is a time of peace</i>
<i> on earth.</i>

00:05.039 --> 00:06.304
<i> At the critch house,</i>

00:06.306 --> 00:08.239
<i> It was just another excuse</i>
<i> to argue.</i>

00:08.241 --> 00:09.908
- Loosen up that garland, mary.

00:09.910 --> 00:12.710
What are you trying to do,
decorate it or hang it?

00:12.747 --> 00:15.147
- Ugh! I hate this packin'
thing!

00:15.282 --> 00:17.149
<i> Why can't we have a real tree?</i>

00:17.284 --> 00:20.185
Practically live in the woods.
- Real trees are death traps!

00:20.187 --> 00:23.121
You ever hear of forest fires?
They all begin with real trees.

00:23.190 --> 00:25.124
<i> Adult mark: Deck the halls</i>
<i> with boughs of plastic.</i>

00:25.259 --> 00:27.593
<i> - Good god! Will somebody</i>
<i> pass me my toolkit?</i>

00:27.728 --> 00:29.461
<i> Adult mark: The old man's</i>
<i> toolbox -</i>

00:29.596 --> 00:31.730
<i> A cookie tin filled with</i>
<i> some nails, some tape,</i>

00:31.865 --> 00:33.665
<i> A flat head screwdriver,</i>
<i> some buttons,</i>

00:33.734 --> 00:35.167
<i> And a rusty hinge.</i>

00:35.302 --> 00:37.436
<i> It was as useless</i>
<i> as the old man himself.</i>

00:37.571 --> 00:39.938
Pop: That's crooked.
Down a bit on the left! Down!

00:40.007 --> 00:42.040
- Christ on a cracker!
[knock at the door]

00:42.076 --> 00:43.875
- Who the frig could that be?
[door clicks open]

00:43.944 --> 00:45.176
<i>High voice: Any mummers allowed</i>
<i> in?</i>

00:45.212 --> 00:48.646
- [excited] oh, mummers!
Pop: Oh my god! [laughs]

00:48.682 --> 00:51.416
<i>Adult mark: Mummering is an old</i>
<i> newfoundland tradition.</i>

00:51.419 --> 00:54.419
<i> You throw together a costume</i>
<i> from things around the house -</i>

00:54.422 --> 00:56.955
<i> Old clothes,</i>
<i> a pillowcase for a mask -</i>

00:57.024 --> 00:59.792
<i> And go door-to-door</i>
<i>getting booze from neighbours</i>

00:59.927 --> 01:01.226
<i> Who would otherwise</i>
<i> never let you in.</i>

01:01.295 --> 01:03.362
<i> [clapping]</i>
<i>it's like Halloween for drunks.</i>

01:03.497 --> 01:05.163
- It's all right,
don't be frightened.

01:05.298 --> 01:08.033
<i> It's somebody we already know.</i>
<i> We just gotta guess who it is.</i>

01:08.168 --> 01:10.636
- But everyone we know
is already here.

01:10.771 --> 01:12.204
This is like a home invasion.

01:12.339 --> 01:14.005
- There'll be none o' that.

01:14.075 --> 01:15.974
All right, reveal yourself!
Dick, is that you?

01:15.976 --> 01:17.375
- What's the matter, mike?

01:17.411 --> 01:19.645
Don't know your own brother?

01:19.780 --> 01:21.880
- Uncle brendan!
[laughs excitedly]

01:21.949 --> 01:23.449
Both: [laughing]

01:23.584 --> 01:25.117
- Dad has a brother?

01:25.119 --> 01:27.385
<i> Adult mark: I had no idea</i>
<i> that I even had an uncle.</i>

01:27.387 --> 01:29.388
<i> While dad stayed behind</i>
<i> caring for their parents,</i>

01:29.523 --> 01:31.222
<i> Brendan had travelled</i>
<i> the world.</i>

01:31.258 --> 01:32.825
<i> Pop: Look at you.</i>

01:32.960 --> 01:34.793
<i> Adult mark: The very mention</i>
<i> of his name would send dad</i>

01:34.795 --> 01:37.595
<i> Into a tizzy and so...</i>
<i>His name was never mentioned.</i>

01:37.631 --> 01:39.297
Pop: Have you lost weight

01:39.299 --> 01:41.633
Or is it just your brother
that's getting fatter?

01:41.635 --> 01:43.601
<i> Brendan: Oh. [laughs]</i>

01:43.637 --> 01:45.303
If I had a woman like mary
cooking for me,

01:45.305 --> 01:47.072
I'd be fat too, dad!

01:47.141 --> 01:49.674
- Oh, brendan, you always had
a way with words. [chuckles]

01:49.676 --> 01:52.110
Brendan: And little mike,
who's not so little anymore!

01:52.146 --> 01:54.613
My god, you've grown
like a tapeworm.

01:54.682 --> 01:56.715
And this must be uh... Uh, uh,

01:56.784 --> 01:58.750
The other one!

01:58.752 --> 02:00.752
- Mark. I don't believe
we've met.

02:00.821 --> 02:02.220
<i>- Oh, that's 'cause last time</i>
<i> I saw you,</i>

02:02.289 --> 02:04.022
You were just a baby.
Go on!

02:04.024 --> 02:05.524
I'm your uncle! Give us a hug.
Arrrrgh!

02:05.659 --> 02:07.292
Jeez, mike, can't believe you
didn't send

02:07.294 --> 02:09.027
So much as a picture.

02:09.029 --> 02:10.828
Mike sr.: Hard to do without
an address, brother.

02:10.865 --> 02:12.631
<i> Pop: Yeah, well, he's hard</i>
<i> to track down</i>

02:12.700 --> 02:15.567
With all his jet setting.
Where are you these days?

02:15.603 --> 02:17.735
- All over the world, dad.

02:17.771 --> 02:19.972
Regina, fort mac...
Pop: Oh!

02:19.974 --> 02:21.506
- Miramichi.
- Oh.

02:21.509 --> 02:23.508
- So, you'll just be passing
through then, I take it?

02:23.511 --> 02:25.310
- Just a quick stop.
Gotta head downtown now,

02:25.379 --> 02:27.112
<i>See if I can find myself a...</i>

02:27.181 --> 02:29.314
Place to crash for the night.

02:29.350 --> 02:31.516
- Uh, there's vacancy
at the skyline motel.

02:31.552 --> 02:33.451
- Uncle brendan can stay
in my room with me.

02:33.487 --> 02:36.087
<i> - Oh! Great! You can tell me</i>
<i> about all the girls</i>

02:36.123 --> 02:38.256
<i> You got on the go, hey?</i>
<i> [laughs]</i>

02:38.325 --> 02:40.725
This calls for a toast.
You got any liquor, brother?

02:40.794 --> 02:42.728
- Dad only drinks the wine
in church.

02:42.863 --> 02:45.330
Pop: Mike, there's a bottle of
rum in the trunk in my room.

02:45.332 --> 02:46.798
<i> Go get it.</i>

02:46.934 --> 02:48.900
Not every day I get to drink
with my son.

02:48.969 --> 02:50.335
- Ha, ha, ha!

02:50.371 --> 02:52.871
That garland's a mess.
Pop: Ah!

02:52.873 --> 02:54.239
<i> [garland rustles]</i>

02:54.241 --> 02:56.608
<i> Ah! Perfect!</i>

03:00.180 --> 03:01.747
- Why didn't you tell me
I had an uncle?

03:01.749 --> 03:03.482
- You never missed much,
believe me.

03:03.617 --> 03:05.483
<i> Mary: [muttering] gonna need</i>
<i> more molasses, more ham,</i>

03:05.553 --> 03:08.186
More margarine, more potatoes...
- I wouldn't count on him

03:08.189 --> 03:10.021
Sticking around very long,
mary.

03:10.090 --> 03:11.856
<i> Pop: What? There's nothing</i>
<i> wrong with family</i>

03:11.892 --> 03:13.859
Wanting to be home
for christmas.

03:13.861 --> 03:16.294
I mean, give him a break, b'y.

03:16.330 --> 03:18.563
Mike sr.: A break?! His whole
life has been a break.

03:18.566 --> 03:20.999
All that man does is take,
take, take!

03:21.134 --> 03:22.901
- Figure'd I give you
your presents now.

03:23.036 --> 03:24.436
No sense trying to hide
anything

03:24.438 --> 03:26.371
In a house this small.
[chuckles]

03:26.373 --> 03:28.473
[inhales and exhales deeply,
wrapping paper crinkles]

03:28.609 --> 03:30.341
Mike!

03:30.377 --> 03:32.243
<i> [rustling] oh!</i>

03:33.781 --> 03:36.581
Pop.
- Oh, no! Really?

03:36.584 --> 03:40.084
[wrapping paper rustles
and tears]

03:40.120 --> 03:41.620
- That's a fondue set!

03:41.622 --> 03:44.455
For dipping bread in cheese.

03:44.457 --> 03:46.924
- You mean like fingers?
[wrapping paper rips]

03:46.961 --> 03:49.327
Pop: Oh my! A clock-radio!

03:49.363 --> 03:52.331
Ah, you see, mike?
It's okay for a son

03:52.466 --> 03:54.466
To give his father a little
present now and then.

03:54.535 --> 03:57.402
- Yeah, like free room and
board for a couple of decades?

03:57.404 --> 03:59.270
- Well, I wouldn't wanna
insult you

03:59.306 --> 04:01.673
By offering ya rent,
ya stunned ass!

04:01.709 --> 04:05.310
Brendan: This is just a small
token of my appreciation

04:05.445 --> 04:07.546
For letting me stay here.
- Oh...

04:07.548 --> 04:09.414
You don't need
to appreciate us,

04:09.416 --> 04:11.650
We're your family!

04:11.785 --> 04:14.052
<i> [wrapping paper tears]</i>

04:15.889 --> 04:18.222
- Springsteen's box set?!
Pop: What?

04:18.259 --> 04:19.691
- That's too much, now,
brendan.

04:19.826 --> 04:22.226
- Well, nothing's too good
for my little roomie.

04:22.263 --> 04:25.396
Now, you didn't think I forgot
about my other nephew, did ya?

04:26.767 --> 04:29.334
♪♪♪

04:29.403 --> 04:31.703
[clap, giggles gleefully]
- [frustrated exhale]

04:31.772 --> 04:35.040
[paper tears]
- a switcheroo-bot...?

04:35.175 --> 04:37.775
Is that supposed to be like
a transformer?

04:37.811 --> 04:41.246
- Mark. What do you say
to your uncle?

04:41.248 --> 04:43.315
<i> Adult mark: I hope you kept</i>
<i> the receipt?</i>

04:43.317 --> 04:44.783
- [weakly] thanks.

04:44.785 --> 04:46.617
<i> Adult mark: I was loyal</i>
<i> to my father.</i>

04:46.654 --> 04:48.486
Mary: [chuckles]

04:48.488 --> 04:50.388
[gasps] oh, brendan.

04:51.458 --> 04:55.260
Oh! It's gorgeous! [gasps]

04:55.262 --> 04:56.795
<i> Brendon: [chuckles happily]</i>

04:56.797 --> 04:58.463
- Oh, it must've cost
a fortune!

04:58.532 --> 05:00.298
- Oh, I'm sure it's nothing

05:00.301 --> 05:01.799
Compared to what mike
has for ya.

05:01.835 --> 05:03.802
- Oh, we don't bother with
gifts after all these years.

05:03.871 --> 05:05.737
- We exchange cards.

05:05.806 --> 05:08.273
I thought you said cards
were more special than gifts.

05:08.275 --> 05:10.208
Brendan: You've still got a lot
to learn about women.

05:10.344 --> 05:11.409
[laughs]

05:11.445 --> 05:13.545
- Yeah.

05:13.547 --> 05:15.447
- Oh, it's-it's-it's too much.

05:15.582 --> 05:17.949
Here, I... I can't.
- What?!

05:17.951 --> 05:19.884
- For god's sake,
keep the coat.

05:19.953 --> 05:22.354
Mike, don't be such
a bloody sook.

05:22.356 --> 05:24.823
- It's not up to me.
It's your gift.

05:24.892 --> 05:27.092
- That's the spirit.
- Well...

05:27.227 --> 05:29.494
Maybe just this once? Hmm?

05:29.530 --> 05:31.363
Brendan: [chuckles]

05:31.365 --> 05:32.397
- [sighs appreciatively] oh...

05:32.532 --> 05:34.633
<i> Pop: That fits like a glove,</i>
<i> mary.</i>

05:34.635 --> 05:36.835
[liquor pours]
- mike! You don't drink.

05:36.904 --> 05:39.037
- Maybe just this once.

05:39.172 --> 05:41.706
Brendan: Jesus.
Mary: Oh! Oh... No!

05:41.742 --> 05:43.375
Oh, look!

05:43.510 --> 05:44.876
They left the security tag
on it.

05:44.912 --> 05:46.912
Oh, I'll just bring it back
to ayre's.

05:46.914 --> 05:49.313
- Don't you worry about that,
my dear.

05:49.350 --> 05:52.384
Nothing I can't get into
with a butter knife.

05:52.386 --> 05:53.919
Ungh!
[security tag clicks]

05:53.921 --> 05:55.987
- Huh! [laughs]
- nothin' to it!

05:56.023 --> 05:58.724
Now... How about that drink?

05:59.993 --> 06:01.460
Pop: Ah, there you go!
[chuckles]

06:01.595 --> 06:04.462
♪♪♪

06:04.531 --> 06:05.797
Pop: Ah... [chuckles]
brendan: [gasps] oh ho!

06:05.866 --> 06:07.665
[glass thunks]
pop: [laughs]

06:08.869 --> 06:10.535
<i> Adult mark: As I drifted off</i>
<i> to sleep,</i>

06:10.537 --> 06:13.138
<i> The sound of all the adults</i>
<i> in the house getting tanked</i>

06:13.207 --> 06:16.541
<i> Somehow made me feel safer</i>
<i> than I'd ever felt in my life.</i>

06:18.945 --> 06:20.846
[school bell rings]

06:20.848 --> 06:22.480
<i> Sister margaret: I know</i>
<i> everyone is excited</i>

06:22.549 --> 06:24.716
For santa claus.
- Am I?

06:24.718 --> 06:26.551
- [gasps, then sighs]
student: [gasp] geez!

06:26.553 --> 06:28.220
Hello, sister.

06:28.222 --> 06:30.254
I was just talking to the
children about christmas.

06:30.290 --> 06:34.092
- And where in the bible would
I find santa claus, sister?

06:38.331 --> 06:40.499
Children, I want to talk to you

06:40.634 --> 06:43.635
About keeping christ
in christmas.

06:45.773 --> 06:48.072
[chalk scrapes]

06:49.943 --> 06:52.777
That's christmas, or...

06:54.047 --> 06:56.180
[chalk taps and scrapes]

06:56.216 --> 06:57.916
Christ mass, not xmas.

06:59.553 --> 07:03.054
When you say "xmas,"
you are crossing out christ.

07:04.425 --> 07:06.257
[chalk scrapes]

07:06.293 --> 07:09.961
And what is an x
but a sideways cross,

07:11.131 --> 07:13.331
Or...

07:13.333 --> 07:15.934
[chalk scrapes]
a crucifix.

07:15.936 --> 07:17.535
<i> Student: [clears throat]</i>

07:17.604 --> 07:20.505
Every time you write xmas,
boys and girls,

07:21.742 --> 07:25.576
You are literally
crucifying jesus.

07:27.547 --> 07:30.548
Ho, ho, hosanna in the highest.

07:30.617 --> 07:32.316
[church bell tolls]

07:32.452 --> 07:34.085
<i>Adult mark: Whatever happened</i>
<i> to rudolph?</i>

07:34.154 --> 07:36.053
<i> Sister margaret: Well,</i>
<i> that was uh... Festive.</i>

07:36.089 --> 07:37.622
[chuckles]

07:37.624 --> 07:40.992
Sister rose has a point
buried in there somewhere.

07:41.028 --> 07:44.929
Christmas is the baby jesus'
birthday party, not yours.

07:44.965 --> 07:47.098
That is why it is better
to give a gift

07:47.134 --> 07:48.767
Than to receive one.

07:48.902 --> 07:50.835
<i> So, we are having</i>
<i> a hamper drive,</i>

07:50.838 --> 07:53.471
<i> Collecting donations of toys</i>
<i> for needy children.</i>

07:53.507 --> 07:56.174
I need some volunteens
to help.

07:56.176 --> 07:57.909
Any volunteens?

07:58.044 --> 07:59.611
<i> Oh!</i>

07:59.680 --> 08:01.846
- Hate to lose out
on a technicality,

08:01.882 --> 08:03.614
But... We're not teens.

08:03.650 --> 08:05.283
But we'd love to help.

08:05.285 --> 08:07.184
- Ha! What a bunch of elf
suck-holes.

08:07.221 --> 08:10.121
<i> Sister margaret: And fox.</i>
<i> Welcome to the volunteens.</i>

08:10.123 --> 08:13.124
Maybe you'll learn to be
a little more considerate.

08:13.126 --> 08:14.759
<i> Student: [clears throat]</i>

08:14.795 --> 08:18.462
[east coast-flavoured
"jingle bells" plays]

08:18.499 --> 08:20.031
Mike sr.: [groaning]

08:20.166 --> 08:22.333
<i> ♪ jingle all the way,</i>
<i> oh what fun... ♪</i>

08:22.369 --> 08:24.202
- God, mike.

08:25.605 --> 08:27.471
<i>♪ jingle bells, jingle bells,</i>
<i> jingle all the way... ♪</i>

08:27.508 --> 08:29.073
You sick?

08:29.142 --> 08:31.609
<i> ♪ oh what fun it is to ride</i>
<i> in a one-horse open sleigh ♪</i>

08:31.645 --> 08:34.145
[shocked] jesus murphy, no...

08:34.147 --> 08:36.814
You're hungover!
- Yeah, well, so are you!

08:36.850 --> 08:39.383
- No, I'm still drunk,
it's different.

08:40.487 --> 08:42.020
Why, if I'd known you were
around the sauce,

08:42.022 --> 08:44.055
I woulda dragged you down
to the legion last night!

08:44.091 --> 08:45.890
I dj-ed their christmas party

08:45.893 --> 08:48.426
And I did not skimp
on the david bowie.

08:48.428 --> 08:50.495
What a night!

08:50.564 --> 08:53.765
I went home with fifty dollars
and leanne lush.

08:53.834 --> 08:55.500
[clacks teeth,
then sucks his teeth]

08:55.635 --> 08:57.501
I'm busier than a bayman
with two woodstoves these days,

08:57.538 --> 08:59.437
What with all the...
The christmas parties

08:59.573 --> 09:01.439
And events the station
has me doin'.

09:01.508 --> 09:04.042
The money's good,
but the hours are a nightmare.

09:04.044 --> 09:06.711
- You know, I could cover some
of those shifts for ya, dick.

09:06.713 --> 09:08.780
- You?

09:08.849 --> 09:11.182
You turn your nose up
at this stuff, mike.

09:11.184 --> 09:13.851
- I need to pick up a little
bit o' extra gift money, okay?

09:13.921 --> 09:16.321
Share the wealth, hey?
It's christmas after all.

09:17.457 --> 09:18.856
♪ ...To ride in a one-horse
open sleigh ♪

09:18.892 --> 09:20.792
♪ jingle bells,
jingle bells... ♪

09:20.794 --> 09:22.794
- Well, there is one gig
I'm trying to get out of.

09:22.929 --> 09:24.862
The money's good,

09:24.898 --> 09:27.999
But trust me,
you wouldn't want it.

09:28.134 --> 09:29.801
<i> ♪ open sleigh! Yup!</i>

09:29.936 --> 09:32.003
[indistinct chatter,
christmas music plays softly]

09:32.072 --> 09:33.805
- God, that thing's so lame.

09:33.874 --> 09:37.274
<i>Ritchie: I mean, why ask a tree</i>
<i> what you want for christmas</i>

09:37.311 --> 09:39.877
When santa is around
the corner?

09:39.913 --> 09:43.214
<i> Happy tree: Good god!</i>
<i> A barbie dream house?!</i>

09:43.283 --> 09:44.915
<i> That's much too expensive!</i>

09:44.952 --> 09:48.019
<i>When I was your age, you'd be</i>
<i> lucky to get an orange.</i>

09:48.088 --> 09:50.422
<i> Kids these days.</i>
<i> Spoiled rotten!</i>

09:50.424 --> 09:52.691
[instrumental "I saw three
ships" plays in the mall]

09:53.794 --> 09:54.893
- Dad?

09:58.298 --> 10:00.031
<i> Adult mark: While ritchie</i>
<i> collected the toys,</i>

10:00.166 --> 10:02.133
<i> I was focused on the tree.</i>

10:02.268 --> 10:04.802
- Dad? Are you in there?

10:04.871 --> 10:06.604
<i>Mike sr.: What? Good god, no!</i>

10:06.606 --> 10:08.773
- [sighs] I can tell
it's your voice.

10:08.908 --> 10:10.708
<i> Mike sr.: No, this is</i>
<i> the happy tree.</i>

10:10.744 --> 10:12.677
<i> End of discussion, mark!</i>
<i> Go home!</i>

10:12.812 --> 10:14.779
- How'd you know my name then?
- Dammit!

10:14.781 --> 10:16.714
- Why are you inside
the happy tree?

10:16.750 --> 10:18.883
- I'm trying to earn a little
bit of extra money

10:18.885 --> 10:20.418
For christmas.
Don't tell your mother.

10:20.454 --> 10:22.920
<i> Or your idiot uncle,</i>
<i> for god's sake.</i>

10:22.990 --> 10:25.456
- You're too old to talk
to the happy tree, doofus.

10:25.492 --> 10:27.859
<i> Happy tree: Uh, hello, fox.</i>
<i> How's your christmas?</i>

10:27.861 --> 10:30.395
- Shut up, tree!
You're... You're lame!

10:30.397 --> 10:31.696
Come on.

10:31.765 --> 10:33.564
- How'd that tree know my name?

10:33.634 --> 10:34.932
- I know, right?

10:36.003 --> 10:37.769
- These toys kinda suck.

10:37.771 --> 10:39.671
<i> Mark: Imagine waking up</i>
<i> on christmas day</i>

10:39.806 --> 10:41.773
And this is all you had
to play with?

10:41.775 --> 10:43.474
[bear tumbles]

10:43.610 --> 10:44.742
Ow...

10:44.778 --> 10:46.644
[plastic bag rustles]

10:46.647 --> 10:48.279
- What was that for?

10:48.348 --> 10:50.348
- Probably saw someone
she knows.

10:52.519 --> 10:53.818
[blues music plays softly]

